The article announces three nominations and appointments made by the United States government. J. Mark Burkhalter has been nominated to be the Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary of the United States to the Kingdom of Norway. He has a background in public policy and regulation, as well as experience in government and real estate development.

William A. Douglass has been nominated to be the Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary of the United States to the Commonwealth of the Bahamas. He is an entrepreneur and philanthropist, having founded and managed K2 Advisors. He has also served on various non-profit boards.

Eric J. Soskin has been nominated to be the Inspector General of the Department of Transportation. He has extensive experience in the Department of Justice, including serving as Senior Trial Counsel and Policy Counsel. He has a strong educational background, with degrees from Williams College and Harvard Law School.